# Form Builder

API-driven form system in `lib/core/form_builder/`. Field definitions come from the backend — the UI renders itself from the data. Never hardcode form fields in views.

## File structure
```
lib/
  core/
    form_builder/
      fn_form_field.dart        # FNFormField model + FieldSelectValues
      form_validators.dart      # FormValidators mixin
      form_exceptions.dart      # ValidateException
      form_field_adapter.dart   # Parses API response into List<FNFormField>
      fn_form_builder.dart      # Core widget — renders fields from list
      form_fields.dart          # FormFieldsBuilderPage — form + submit button
      form_page_template.dart   # Scaffold wrapper around FormFieldsBuilderPage
      form_field_widget.dart    # FormFieldInput — text/email/number/password
      select_value_widget.dart  # SelectValue — popup list picker
      radio_input_field.dart    # RadioInputField — radio group
      remove_focus_on_tap.dart  # Dismiss keyboard on tap outside
```

---

## FNFormField

The model representing a single form field. Comes from the API via `FormFieldAdapter`.

```dart
FNFormField(
  attribute: 'email',           // key in the DTO sent to the API
  label: 'Email address',       // displayed label
  type: 'email',                // determines which widget is rendered
  hint: 'Enter your email',     // placeholder text
  required: true,               // toggles validation
  suffix: '',                   // optional suffix text (e.g. 'kg', '%')
  value: 'prefilled@value.com', // pre-filled value (optional)
  conditionedBy: 'role',        // show only when another field equals conditionValue
  conditionValue: 'admin',      // the value that makes this field visible
  textInputAction: "next",           // always a string — parsed to TextInputAction by adapter
  values: [                     // options for select/radio types
    FieldSelectValues(label: 'Option A', value: 'a', image: ''),
  ],
)
```

### Supported field types
Field types are defined by the `FieldType` enum in `fn_form_field.dart`. Always use the string name in maps — the adapter parses it to the enum.

| string | FieldType | Widget rendered |
|---|---|---|
| `"text"` | `FieldType.text` | `FormFieldInput` (text keyboard) |
| `"email"` | `FieldType.email` | `FormFieldInput` (email keyboard) |
| `"number"` | `FieldType.number` | `FormFieldInput` (numeric keyboard) |
| `"password"` | `FieldType.password` | `FormFieldInput` (obscured) |
| `"select"` | `FieldType.select` | `SelectValue` (popup list) |
| `"radio"` | `FieldType.radio` | `RadioInputField` (radio group) |
| `"address_lookup"` | `FieldType.addressLookup` | placeholder |
| `"picture"` | `FieldType.picture` | placeholder |

Unknown type strings fall back to `FieldType.text` — the field renders as a plain text input so it's always visible. If a field looks wrong, check the `type` string matches a `FieldType` name.

To add a new field type: add it to the `FieldType` enum, handle it in `FnFormBuilder._buildField()` switch, and add a validator to `FormValidators`.

