## Defining fields locally

Fields are defined as plain Dart maps and parsed via `FormFieldAdapter`. This is the standard pattern — fields do not need to come from the API.

```dart
final loginFields = FormFieldAdapter().fromJsonToList([
  {
    "attribute": "email",
    "label": "Email",
    "hint": "What is your email address?",
    "type": "email",
    "required": true,
    "textInputAction": "next",
  },
  {
    "attribute": "password",
    "label": "Password",
    "hint": "",
    "type": "password",
    "required": true,
    "textInputAction": "go",
  },
]);
```

Define fields at the top of the controller file, next to the atom. They are static data — not inside a method.

---

## Parsing fields from API

Use `FormFieldAdapter` to parse the API response into a list of fields:

```dart
final fields = FormFieldAdapter().fromJsonToList(response.data['fields']);
```

---

## Rendering a form

### FormFieldsBuilderPage — form + submit button
Use this when embedding a form inside an existing screen:

```dart
FormFieldsBuilderPage(
  formFields: fields,
  ctaLabel: 'Save changes',
  onSubmit: (Map<String, dynamic> dto) async {
    final result = await controller.updateProfile(dto);
    if (result is Success) Navigator.pop(context);
  },
)
```

With pre-filled values from an existing entity:
```dart
FormFieldsBuilderPage(
  entity: userEntity,   // implements Entity — provides getAttribute()
  formFields: fields,
  onSubmit: (dto) async => controller.updateProfile(dto),
)
```

### FormPageTemplate — full Scaffold with AppBar
Use this when the form is a standalone page:

```dart
FormPageTemplate(
  formFields: fields,
  ctaLabel: 'Register',
  onSubmit: (dto) async => controller.register(dto),
)

// Edit mode — AppBar title changes to "Editing"
FormPageTemplate(
  entity: existingEntity,
  formFields: fields,
  onSubmit: (dto) async => controller.update(dto),
)
```

