## Conditional fields

A field can be shown/hidden based on the value of another field:

```dart
FNFormField(
  attribute: 'company_name',
  type: 'text',
  label: 'Company name',
  conditionedBy: 'account_type',   // watches this attribute
  conditionValue: 'business',      // visible only when account_type == 'business'
  ...
)
```

The controlling field must appear before the conditioned field in the list. The conditioned field animates in/out with `AnimatedOpacity`.

---

## The DTO

`FormFieldsBuilderPage` builds a `Map<String, dynamic>` DTO automatically from the field list. Keys are `field.attribute` values. The DTO is passed to `onSubmit` when the form is valid.

You do not need to build the DTO manually — just handle `onSubmit`:

```dart
onSubmit: (Map<String, dynamic> dto) async {
  // dto = { 'email': 'user@example.com', 'name': 'John', ... }
  await controller.submit(dto);
}
```

---

## Validation

Validation is automatic — each field type has a validator in `FormValidators`. Validation runs on user interaction (`AutovalidateMode.onUserInteraction`). On submit, all fields are validated and a snackbar is shown if any fail.

To skip validation for a field, set `required: false`.

---

## Rules
- Never use raw `TextFormField`, `DropdownButton`, or `RadioListTile` directly in feature views — always go through the form builder
- Never hardcode form fields in views — define them as `List<FNFormField>` in the controller or parse from API
- Never build the DTO manually — `FormFieldsBuilderPage` handles it
- `FormPageTemplate` is a thin Scaffold wrapper — all logic lives in `FormFieldsBuilderPage`
- Always pass `textInputAction` as a string (`"next"`, `"go"`, `"done"`) — never as `TextInputAction.next` directly
- To add a new field type: add the type string to `FnFormBuilder._builder()` map and add a validator to `FormValidators`
